<i>Make a fast buck if we had to...</i>

22:46.866 --> 22:51.212
<i>that progressed into getting arrested, and...</i>

22:51.370 --> 22:55.091
<i>The struggle that you have within yourself,
the loss, you know what I mean?</i>

22:55.249 --> 22:59.299
<i>The disappointment in yourself. The anger
that turns into disappointment. The despair.</i>

22:59.461 --> 23:02.305
<i>It's like the guy sitting in the bar,
and a priest walks in.</i>

23:02.464 --> 23:04.011
The guy says, 
"Hey, wait a minute.

23:04.174 --> 23:08.395
I hate to tell you this, don't waste your time, 
but I happen to know there's no God."

23:08.554 --> 23:10.227
The priest says, 
"Yeah, how's that?"

23:10.389 --> 23:13.734
The guy says,
"I was an explorer in the North Pole.

23:13.893 --> 23:17.318
I got caught in a blinding storm once.
Freezing. I was blinded.

23:17.479 --> 23:21.109
Freezing to death. And I prayed,
'If there's a God, save me now.'

23:21.275 --> 23:22.777
Now, God didn't come."

23:22.943 --> 23:26.664
And the priest says, you know, "How's that? 
You're alive. He must've saved you."

23:26.822 --> 23:28.324
He says, 
"God never showed up.

23:28.490 --> 23:32.495
An Eskimo came along,
Took me back to his camp and saved me."

23:32.661 --> 23:35.710
That's Janice. She's my wife
and she's sitting right there,

23:36.498 --> 23:38.796
She's my Eskimo.

24:26.340 --> 24:28.058
- How you doing?
- Hey.

25:02.918 --> 25:03.919
Excuse me?

25:04.670 --> 25:06.343
Are you doing laundry?

25:07.548 --> 25:08.970
Huh?

25:09.258 --> 25:11.932
I just wondered if you had any change.
The machine is out.

25:13.721 --> 25:15.894
- Can't help you. Sorry.
- Okay.

25:17.599 --> 25:19.772
I can just hang them up
when I get home.

25:49.882 --> 25:51.384
You all right?

25:52.384 --> 25:54.227
I'm fine. I'm just--

25:54.386 --> 25:56.013
Are you sure?

26:00.434 --> 26:01.481
You okay?

26:02.061 --> 26:05.531
Yeah, I'm fine. I'm fine, thank you.
I'm fine, yeah.

26:05.689 --> 26:07.441
Well, this is embarrassing.

26:07.608 --> 26:10.077
No, you got nothing
to be embarrassed for.

26:11.862 --> 26:13.864
Do you need help?

26:14.448 --> 26:16.542
I'm just having a bad week.

26:18.702 --> 26:20.500
I understand.

26:21.789 --> 26:24.042
I like to have a good cry
at the nail salon.

26:26.502 --> 26:30.723
Just open right up to the ladies.
They're very understanding.

26:30.881 --> 26:34.010
But, you know,
you like the Laundromat, so that's fine.

26:40.641 --> 26:44.487
Hey, why don't you let me
buy you a drink.

26:44.645 --> 26:47.114
Make up for letting you down
with the quarters.

26:47.272 --> 26:49.866
You know, see if we can turn
your week around.

26:51.026 --> 26:52.699
What's the worst that could happen?

26:52.861 --> 26:54.158
<i>FBI! Open the door!</i>

26:54.488 --> 26:55.740
Open the door!

26:58.367 --> 26:59.710
Fuck.

27:05.874 --> 27:07.046
Fuck.

27:07.209 --> 27:09.211
Fucking cocksucker. 
Get off him.

27:22.558 --> 27:23.901
Jesus Christ, Henry.

27:24.643 --> 27:26.771
Oxy, guns?

27:27.563 --> 27:29.190
It's like townie Christmas.

27:32.151 --> 27:35.781
Minimum federal sentencing,
10 years.

27:38.574 --> 27:39.826
You're gonna need a friend.

27:41.910 --> 27:43.753
And she ain't it.

27:44.872 --> 27:48.422
Great girl, though.
She really loves you, I can tell.

27:49.334 --> 27:52.554
Good news for you is you have an alibi
for the Cambridge job.

27:52.713 --> 27:56.468
The good news for me
is I bet you know something about it.

27:57.718 --> 27:59.937
Everyone does trucks.

28:00.596 --> 28:02.849
These guys beat the alarm
for the vault.

28:03.348 --> 28:05.066
- Yeah?
- It's what I heard.

28:05.225 --> 28:08.946
A kid, he gets into the junction box.

28:17.946 --> 28:19.948
- This is nice.
- Yeah, it's a good place.

28:20.115 --> 28:23.460
A guy I played hockey with for a long time
is one of the managers here.

28:23.619 --> 28:26.463
Oh, yeah? That's nice.

28:27.456 --> 28:29.174
So, what do you do for work?

28:31.126 --> 28:32.423
Boston Sand and Gravel.

28:32.586 --> 28:35.590
I break rocks.
Punch a ticket at the end of the day...

28:35.756 --> 28:38.635
slide down the back of a brontosaurus
like Fred Flintstone.

28:38.800 --> 28:39.892
Call it a night.

28:41.220 --> 28:43.143
- Can I ask you something?
- You sure can.

28:43.305 --> 28:45.774
I volunteer at the Boys & Girls Club
in Charlestown--

28:45.933 --> 28:47.105
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

28:47.267 --> 28:51.192
As a kickball pitcher since they haven't
been able to afford any ice for the rink.

28:51.355 --> 28:54.029
Embarrassing, City won't put
any money into that place.

28:54.191 --> 28:57.991
Yeah, I know. Yeah, well, some of the kids
were calling me a toonie.

28:58.528 --> 29:02.158
It just means a yuppie. Someone who's not 
from Charlestown, that's all.

29:02.324 --> 29:05.498
- Of course it does.
- They're just being punks.

29:05.661 --> 29:06.708
- A yuppie.
- Yeah.

29:06.870 --> 29:10.215
- So where does the word come from?
- Uh...

29:10.499 --> 29:12.376
It comes from back in the '90s, like...

29:12.542 --> 29:15.136
the toonies supplied all the tunes
to Charlestown...

29:15.295 --> 29:19.175
because once they moved in
the townies stole all their car stereos.

29:19.341 --> 29:21.719
So all of a sudden,
everyone in Charlestown...

29:21.885 --> 29:25.185
had a Blaupunkt in their car,
you know what I mean?

29:25.847 --> 29:26.894
Anyway.

29:28.350 --> 29:30.478
So do your parents still live
in Charlestown?

29:30.852 --> 29:33.480
No. My mother moved away.

29:33.647 --> 29:37.527
My father lives out in the suburbs.

29:39.278 --> 29:41.531
Yeah. He don't get out much.

29:42.114 --> 29:45.084
- No, I mean where did you grow up?
- Marblehead.

29:46.201 --> 29:48.044
Marblehead?

29:48.370 --> 29:49.542
Wow.

29:49.705 --> 29:52.128
Yeah, well,
I represent Marblehead's poor.

29:52.291 --> 29:54.669
- Oh, really?
- Yeah, you were defined by...

29:54.835 --> 29:59.887
whether or not your family owned a boat.
And, well, my family didn't own a boat.

30:00.048 --> 30:03.643
No boat. How could you
look yourself in the mirror?

30:03.802 --> 30:05.475
It's embarrassing.

30:07.389 --> 30:08.641
- I have a boat.
- Oh, yeah?

30:08.807 --> 30:11.401
- Yeah.
- Well, you would do well in Marblehead.

30:11.560 --> 30:15.235
Yeah, maybe. it's not my boat,
it's my friend's boat.

30:15.939 --> 30:17.612
You should...

30:17.774 --> 30:20.368
let me take you for a ride sometime.

30:21.987 --> 30:24.831
- I'd love that. Sometime.
- Yeah.

30:24.990 --> 30:28.494
What about right now?

30:38.920 --> 30:42.515
That's the boat. 
Right there.

30:45.052 --> 30:46.554
Wow.

30:47.763 --> 30:50.437
- Not bad, right?
- Good friends to have.

31:10.452 --> 31:13.331
Here you go.
It's the best cup I could find.

31:14.581 --> 31:16.333
Not too much.

31:16.500 --> 31:18.173
Thank you.

31:21.004 --> 31:23.803
It's nice, right? 
I told you.

31:23.965 --> 31:26.309
Is this where you take all the girls?

31:27.636 --> 31:31.482
I can honestly tell you I have never taken
another girl here in my entire life.

31:31.640 --> 31:34.234
- Oh, yeah?
- Mm-hm. That's the truth.

31:38.146 --> 31:40.820
Hey, what do you know about
bank robbers?

31:44.319 --> 31:46.822
- What's to know?
- You're from Charlestown.

31:46.988 --> 31:49.082
I figured you grew up 
with some of them.

31:49.533 --> 31:51.877
No, not really. I mean...

31:52.244 --> 31:55.669
A lot of what they say is exaggerated.
I mean, I--

31:57.499 --> 31:59.467
When I was a kid, uh...

32:00.919 --> 32:03.422
we used to go to Wizard's ice cream.

32:03.588 --> 32:05.841
It was across from J.J.'s Bar.

32:06.007 --> 32:08.806
That was where all the big
armored-car guys hung out.

32:08.969 --> 32:12.314
And they were like rock stars
in the neighborhood, you know?

32:12.472 --> 32:15.646
Fancy cars. Pretty girls.

32:15.809 --> 32:21.407
And you heard rumors
about the jobs they pulled.

32:21.565 --> 32:25.866
The big houses they had
in Holbrook or Winthrop.

32:27.195 --> 32:29.914
There was a lot of kids
in the ice-cream shop...

32:30.073 --> 32:33.668
with their noses pressed
against the glass, you know...

32:34.578 --> 32:37.422
who wanted to be like those guys.

32:40.208 --> 32:41.881
I just wanted to play hockey.

32:46.423 --> 32:49.518
Anyway, that's what I know
about bank robbers.

32:55.223 --> 32:59.148
- Hey, Jem. How's it going?
- Hey, B. Can I have a beer? Thanks.

32:59.311 --> 33:00.403
- Oh, shit.
- What up?

33:00.562 --> 33:04.032
- How you doing?
- All right. Sox got rocked.

33:06.651 --> 33:08.244
What's going on?

33:11.740 --> 33:13.788
You, uh, check on that thing?

33:13.950 --> 33:15.076
What?

33:15.243 --> 33:17.371
The license.

33:18.538 --> 33:21.382
- Yeah.
- And?

33:21.541 --> 33:24.590
Nothing. It's a dead end. 
We're all set.

33:25.378 --> 33:28.006
So no need to remove her
from the equation?

33:28.590 --> 33:31.594
- What?
- You heard me.

33:32.010 --> 33:34.809
What are you, a triggerman now?

33:35.222 --> 33:37.099
Just loose ends, kid.

33:38.683 --> 33:42.278
You're gonna get the fucking electric chair 
brought back over to Charlestown.

33:42.437 --> 33:44.781
Don't be so goddamned panicked,
all right, Dig Dug?

33:44.940 --> 33:48.114
Just, you know, I don't wanna get
backdoored, that's all.

33:48.276 --> 33:51.155
- We're fine. All right?
- All right. We're fine.

33:51.321 --> 33:53.619
- Okay.
- We're fine.

33:56.117 --> 33:58.211
They obviously know
how to work the box.

33:58.370 --> 34:02.420
But I like the way they zapped the BPT
to the D-5 station.

34:02.582 --> 34:04.710
How does one learn how to do that?

34:06.002 --> 34:07.925
Get a job at Vericom.

34:08.088 --> 34:10.716
- Okay.
- Thank you.

34:12.132 --> 34:14.601
All right, let's subpoena work logs,
employee records.

34:14.761 --> 34:16.763
Start with everybody
who lives in the town.

34:16.929 --> 34:18.351
Got it.

34:22.851 --> 34:26.527
Ms. Keesey, it's Agent Frawley.
I have follow-up questions about your case.

34:26.690 --> 34:28.784
Is there somewhere we can meet?

34:29.693 --> 34:32.286
Why didn't you tell me
you lived in Charlestown?

34:32.445 --> 34:33.661
It's on my paperwork.

34:40.954 --> 34:42.331
You don't like your sandwich?

34:43.206 --> 34:47.177
It's the unfortunate nagging suspicion
you get as an FBI agent..

34:47.335 --> 34:50.554
who has put a lot of neighborhood people 
in federal prison...

34:50.714 --> 34:54.389
that someone may have
violated your meal.

34:54.551 --> 34:57.020
Come on, I don't think
anyone would do that.

34:57.178 --> 35:00.398
They throw Tom Fitz off the roof
of Mishawum for cooperating...

35:00.557 --> 35:04.061
and then stand around and taunt him
while he drowned in his own blood.

35:04.519 --> 35:07.022
So I don't think the lunch special
is out of bounds.

35:07.188 --> 35:09.156
Okay.

35:09.899 --> 35:12.322
They lionize criminals...

35:12.485 --> 35:14.533
and complain about crime...

35:14.696 --> 35:16.198
and I'm the bad guy.

35:17.324 --> 35:20.828
This place is one square mile.

35:20.994 --> 35:24.464
You walk into Lewisburg,
there's a hundred townies in there.

35:24.998 --> 35:26.875
Well, I think I'll skip Lewisburg.

35:28.043 --> 35:30.262
Doesn't sound like a fun second date?

35:33.590 --> 35:36.013
If I ask a question,
will you give an honest answer?

35:36.509 --> 35:38.227
It depends on the question.

35:39.054 --> 35:40.647
Am I a suspect?

35:41.473 --> 35:43.896
Would I ask you out
if I thought you were a suspect?

35:44.059 --> 35:45.902
I don't know.

35:46.770 --> 35:49.068
- Would you?
- Not if I wanted a conviction.

35:55.654 --> 35:58.032
I might be seeing someone already.

36:02.077 --> 36:04.455
- What? What is it?
- Stickup.

36:05.080 --> 36:06.798
Chelsea Credit Union.

36:06.956 --> 36:09.050
What would we do without Chelsea?

36:12.545 --> 36:14.343
Anyway, aren't there rules?

36:14.923 --> 36:17.096
Against dating the Vic?
Yeah, there's a rule.

36:17.258 --> 36:18.931
You don't do it.

36:24.140 --> 36:26.359
- There she is.
- Hey.

36:26.518 --> 36:29.021
- All set?
- Yes.

36:31.731 --> 36:34.029
I should have come
get your door for you, huh?

36:34.192 --> 36:37.116
What kind of a guy lets you open
your own door like that?

36:39.447 --> 36:40.699
What?

36:41.658 --> 36:43.535
I have to get something out there...

36:43.702 --> 36:47.172
otherwise I'll be pretending
to listen to you all night...

36:47.330 --> 36:49.833
when really I'm thinking about
something else.

36:51.251 --> 36:52.298
Okay.

36:55.046 --> 36:57.469
A few days ago my bank was robbed.

36:57.632 --> 37:01.182
Four men took it over
and opened the safe.

37:01.594 --> 37:04.643
They took me as a hostage.

37:06.266 --> 37:09.065
They blindfolded me
and drove me around.

37:11.271 --> 37:14.366
And then they stopped and let me out
over at the beach and...

37:15.650 --> 37:19.029
And one of the guys told me...

37:19.279 --> 37:23.000
to walk until I felt the water
on my toes.

37:24.409 --> 37:28.289
It was the longest walk of my life.
I kept thinking I'd step off a cliff.

37:32.584 --> 37:34.928
And then I felt the water.

37:37.797 --> 37:39.674
I'm sorry.

37:40.425 --> 37:42.598
It's not your fault.

37:44.554 --> 37:48.684
Anyway, the FBI guy told me
it would feel like I was in mourning.

37:48.850 --> 37:51.979
FBI? You're working with the FBI?

37:52.145 --> 37:53.567
Mm-hm.

37:54.314 --> 37:56.237
What does that mean?

37:56.483 --> 37:59.737
Guy comes by, checks in on you,
gives you a call? That kind of thing?

38:00.361 --> 38:01.908
Pretty much.

38:02.655 --> 38:06.285
They don't have any suspects?
Any clues? Any leads? Anything like that?

38:06.701 --> 38:09.045
I don't know.
Not that they've told me.

38:09.204 --> 38:12.048
He intimated that they were
scouring Charlestown...

38:13.374 --> 38:16.719
but they were wearing masks, so...

38:17.337 --> 38:19.715
- Shit.
- Mm.

38:21.216 --> 38:24.516
I'm sure I'd recognize their voices
if I heard them again.

38:25.220 --> 38:28.895
I don't know,
might be harder than you think.

38:30.016 --> 38:31.859
At least you weren't hurt.

38:33.895 --> 38:35.363
No.

38:35.939 --> 38:37.566
No, but David was.

38:37.732 --> 38:41.862
My assistant manager, he was assaulted
really badly when the alarm went off.

38:42.403 --> 38:44.656
He's been at Mass Eye and Ear
for a week.

38:44.823 --> 38:46.416
Eye surgery.

38:46.991 --> 38:49.665
And I still haven't been able
to go see him.

38:50.245 --> 38:52.839
I feel like a terrible person.

38:53.832 --> 38:57.177
Then I guess we know
where we're going.

39:11.057 --> 39:12.274
Well, you should come in.

39:12.976 --> 39:15.320
- Yeah?
- Yeah, you should meet him.

39:15.812 --> 39:17.359
All right.

39:18.147 --> 39:19.774
- Hi.
- Hello. Hi.

39:19.941 --> 39:22.820
Oh, hi. Come to my good side.

39:23.611 --> 39:25.579
- Hi.
- Look. You don't look so bad.

39:25.738 --> 39:27.490
- Really?
- Well, you know.

39:27.657 --> 39:28.954
- Hello.
- Hey.

39:29.117 --> 39:31.836
- This is my friend Doug.
- Hi. Nice to meet you.

39:31.995 --> 39:33.872
Nice to meet you. 
I can almost see you.

39:34.038 --> 39:35.381
So...

39:35.623 --> 39:36.795
they're hopeful.

39:36.958 --> 39:39.632
Well, "hopeful" means I may recover...

39:39.794 --> 39:42.172
50 percent of my sight in this eye.

39:42.630 --> 39:45.133
Oh, I just want to get back to work.

39:45.300 --> 39:48.474
I'm gonna give you guys some privacy.
I'll be right outside.

39:53.641 --> 39:55.894
- You heard what happened?
- Huh?

39:56.311 --> 39:58.564
Big takedown robbery.

39:58.813 --> 40:02.192
- Fucking punks laid the guy out.
- Oh, yeah?

40:04.319 --> 40:06.413
It's a good thing you're here.

40:07.280 --> 40:09.078
Those guys could come back.

40:09.741 --> 40:11.334
Yeah.

40:11.534 --> 40:13.957
<i>I lied to the FBI.</i>

40:14.162 --> 40:15.709
<i>What?</i>

40:16.080 --> 40:17.582
When the guy attacked David...

40:17.749 --> 40:20.343
I could see the back of his neck
and he had a tattoo.

40:22.670 --> 40:23.842
Of what?

40:24.297 --> 40:27.471
It was one of those
Fighting Irish tattoos.

40:27.634 --> 40:30.183
I'm afraid if I report it
they'll make me testify.

40:30.345 --> 40:32.689
What do you think I should do?

40:36.184 --> 40:38.357
Tell the FBI.

40:38.853 --> 40:42.699
If the guy's got a record,
and I'm sure he does...

40:42.857 --> 40:45.485
they'll have his tattoos on file.

40:45.777 --> 40:47.950
They'll ring him up the next day.

40:48.112 --> 40:51.116
Robbery, weapons. 
He'll get 30 years.

40:51.282 --> 40:54.832
Course, they'll worry someone's
gonna come looking for the witness.

40:55.119 --> 40:58.874
The FBI will probably want to put you 
in WITSEC, you know, Witness Security.

40:59.040 --> 41:03.090
You know, they'll probably put you somewhere,
like, you know, in Cleveland...

41:03.252 --> 41:05.471
or Arizona, you know,
somewhere safe.

41:07.715 --> 41:09.137
Or...

41:09.467 --> 41:11.265
you could wait.

41:13.221 --> 41:15.223
You have a card.

41:16.057 --> 41:18.401
There's nothing says you gotta 
play it right away.

41:18.559 --> 41:21.688
You're the one who's vulnerable
in this situation right now.

41:22.146 --> 41:24.695
The FBI are just people
like anyone else.

41:24.857 --> 41:27.861
They wanna find the bad guy so they
can go home and nuke their supper.

41:28.027 --> 41:31.076
You have to look out
for yourself, Claire.

41:33.074 --> 41:34.701
Quite an expert.

41:36.703 --> 41:38.250
Not really.

41:39.789 --> 41:41.086
Just watch a lot of TV.

41:42.000 --> 41:43.968
I watch a lot of <i>CSI.</i>

41:44.127 --> 41:47.131
So I'm a really big expert
on all this. I know.

41:47.296 --> 41:50.721
And <i>Miami CSI</i> 
and <i>New York CSI.</i>

41:50.883 --> 41:52.760
All of them, I watch.

41:52.927 --> 41:54.270
You'll be well-prepared.

41:54.429 --> 41:55.806
And <i>Bones.</i>

41:59.183 --> 42:04.986
Do we know each other well enough for me 
to say that this truck is a little much?

42:05.148 --> 42:06.274
It's my work truck.

42:06.441 --> 42:09.615
If you have problems with your Prius
I can throw it in the back.

42:09.777 --> 42:11.779
How did you know I had a Prius?

42:14.407 --> 42:17.786
Took a guess.
I mean, it just seemed like a toonie car.

42:17.952 --> 42:19.795
- Why, do you really have a Prius?
- Yeah.

42:19.954 --> 42:22.332
- Really?
- I had a Prius.

42:22.498 --> 42:25.502
- It got vandalized, of course.
- What happened?

42:25.668 --> 42:29.047
Doesn't matter. Now I'm forced to walk
a mile through the projects.

42:29.213 --> 42:32.592
- There were these guys and they started...
- What?

42:32.759 --> 42:35.638
I'm not sure if it was the same guys
who trashed my car, but--

42:35.803 --> 42:39.307
They started getting, you know--
It started with yelling when I walked by...

42:39.474 --> 42:41.693
and then it got
really aggressive and...

42:41.851 --> 42:43.068
What were they doing?

42:43.227 --> 42:45.400
Once glass bottles
started getting thrown...

42:45.563 --> 42:49.488
I started coming to terms with not being
cool enough to walk through the projects.

42:49.650 --> 42:51.493
They threw bottles at you?

42:51.652 --> 42:55.247
I'm fine. I just have to, you know,
go the long way.

42:55.656 --> 42:57.579
That's all. It doesn't matter.

42:57.742 --> 43:00.291
